+{"id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","title":"Implement epoch, barrier, circuit-breaker, and bulkhead public semantics","description":"The upstream crate exports a substantial epoch family with barrier triggers, context, policies, selection helpers, and resilience controls. ANSI C currently lacks a comparable public epoch/resilience layer even though it materially affects orchestration, fairness, and failure management.","design":"Port the public epoch model in a way that composes with existing runtime/cancel/budget machinery. Include barrier semantics, policy objects, scoped epoch helpers, and explicit error/reporting behavior.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public epoch/resilience APIs exist with clear state/error contracts.\\nB. Unit and property-style tests cover barrier triggers, selection behavior, breaker/bulkhead transitions, and epoch-scoped orchestration.\\nC. A logged end-to-end scenario demonstrates epoch-controlled execution and failure containment.","notes":"Dependencies: foundation task B1 and verification task A3 should land first.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:19.531626700Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:01.459251420Z","closed_at":"2026-03-17T06:55:01.458731232Z","close_reason":"Implemented epoch and circuit-breaker public modules. Epoch: phase-scoped execution with manual/barrier/threshold advance modes, observer notifications, max-phase limits (header + 186-line impl + 13 tests). Circuit breaker: closed/open/half-open state machine with configurable failure/success thresholds, call admission control (header + 165-line impl + 17 tests). Bulkhead already existed in combinator2.h. All 30 new tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","epoch","resilience"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:47.316216820Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:48.023177435Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:48.709870169Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:19.531626700Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:24.493762068Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5","title":"Capability, security, obligation, record, and evidence parity","description":"Several upstream families that make asupersync structurally safe are still missing or shallow in ANSI C: advanced cx capability machinery, security/authenticated surfaces, obligation and record modules, session/link/monitor layers, and evidence/evidence-sink public APIs.","design":"This epic should restore the explicit authority and proof-carrying story of the Rust crate rather than leaving only kernel internals and a few diagnostics helpers.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Missing authority/evidence/record families are represented as real public modules with coherent contracts.\\nB. Security and obligation behavior is covered by unit plus failure-path integration tests.\\nC. Session/link/monitor-style coordination surfaces no longer remain silent omissions.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/cx/*, src/security/*, src/obligation/*, src/record/*, src/evidence.rs, src/evidence_sink.rs, src/link.rs, src/monitor.rs, and session-related exports in src/lib.rs.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:20.291103519Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:04.190535578Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","cx","record","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:20.291103519Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:59.622791584Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:00.575561527Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:01.534808222Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","title":"Complete cx capability flow: caps, registry, macaroon, wrappers, and scope wiring","description":"ANSI C has basic cx headers, but not the richer upstream capability flow with capability wrappers, registries, macaroons/attenuation, and explicit authority propagation helpers. This gap weakens the crate's advertised no-ambient-authority story.","design":"Implement the missing public capability surfaces and thread them through representative runtime/app/network entry points so they are real constraints, not decorative types.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public capability APIs cover attenuation/registration/wrapping flows and fail closed when authority is missing.\\nB. Unit tests cover issuance, attenuation, misuse, and propagation.\\nC. At least one logged scenario proves capability restrictions on a realistic higher-surface operation.","notes":"Coordinate with security and browser/native feature matrices from A2.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.111936107Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T04:34:52.901730862Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T04:34:52.901199084Z","close_reason":"Shipped cx/scope through umbrella+archive, enabled cx unit discovery, added logged capability-wrapping scope vignette, and verified cx binaries","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["capabilities","crate-parity","cx"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:49.405444228Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:50.123965027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:50.818287457Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.111936107Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","title":"Port security, audit, tag, key, context, and authenticated surfaces","description":"The upstream crate exports a real security module with key/context/tag/authenticated types plus audit surfaces. The ANSI C tree needs more than minimal checks or vertical-specific instrumentation if it is going to claim comparable crate-level functionality.","design":"Port public security/audit contracts, including error taxonomy, authority context propagation, authenticated wrappers, and audit/event capture hooks that integrate with evidence/logging.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public security/audit headers and implementations cover the upstream conceptual surface.\\nB. Unit tests cover key/tag/context handling, authenticated wrappers, and negative authorization cases.\\nC. Logged integration flows show audit/evidence output for both accepted and rejected operations.","notes":"Should integrate with C1 and C3 instead of becoming a disconnected helper island.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.943361044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T18:48:04.754399782Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T18:48:04.753881692Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","crate-parity","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:51.527022719Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:52.256469280Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:53.009498774Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.943361044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:25.635031025Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","title":"Port obligation, record, session, and link public parity","description":"Rust exposes rich obligation and record families plus session and link surfaces used for diagnostics, proofs, and long-lived coordination. ANSI C currently has only partial lower-level pieces, leaving a large user-facing and correctness-story gap.","design":"Implement public record types, obligation helpers beyond the raw kernel path, and session/link coordination APIs. Keep observability, monitor, and evidence-sink work in a dedicated sibling task so this bead stays implementable without losing scope.","acceptance_criteria":"A. The missing public record, obligation, session, and link module families exist and integrate with runtime flows.\\nB. Tests cover record lifecycle, session/link behavior, and obligation misuse.\\nC. At least one e2e or smoke lane exercises a realistic session/link flow with detailed logs and failure summaries.","notes":"Coordinate with the new observability/evidence task under the same epic so proof artifacts and runtime records share one coherent contract.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:22.799210276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448641833Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448232799Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","evidence","obligation","record","session"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:53.754722768Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:54.563725663Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:55.384692776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id